import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  

export default class MDXContent extends React.Component {
  constructor(props) {
    super(props)
    this.layout = null
  }
  render() {
    const { components, ...props } = this.props

    return <MDXTag
             name="wrapper"
             
             components={components}><MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`The most basic type of item, literally anything and everything.  All yodata:realestate types are sub-types of Thing.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}><MDXTag name="a" components={components} parentName="p" props={{"href":"https://schema.org/Thing"}}>{`https://schema.org/Thing`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"schemaorg-deviations"}}>{`Schema.org deviations`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Occasionally we deviate from strict schema.org for brevity, clarity and/or convenience. `}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h3" components={components} props={{"id":"identifiers"}}>{`identifiers`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`  Identifier in REflex is a context specific Map<name,value> useful for matching objects across related systems`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="pre" components={components}><MDXTag name="code" components={components} parentName="pre" props={{"className":"language-yaml"}}>{`# Reflex identifier Map
type: Thing
identifier:
    '@context': 'https://context.yodata.io/hsf/reflex'
    ContactID: 1234
    
# strict schema.org equivalent (a bit too wordy)

type: 'https://schema.org/Thing'
identifier: [
    '@context': 'https://context.yodata.io/yodata/hsf/reflex'
    type: PropertyValue
    name: ContactID
    value: 1234
]
`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"example"}}>{`example`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h3" components={components} props={{"id":"minimal"}}>{`minimal`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="pre" components={components}><MDXTag name="code" components={components} parentName="pre" props={{"className":"language-yaml"}}>{`# @context defaults to REflex default context (yodata:realestate)
type: Person
`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h3" components={components} props={{"id":"basic"}}>{`basic`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`most common properties`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="pre" components={components}><MDXTag name="code" components={components} parentName="pre" props={{"className":"language-yaml"}}>{`type: Person
id: 'https://user.example.com/profile/card#me'
name: Bob Jones
url: 'https://bobjones.com'
`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h3" components={components} props={{"id":"complete"}}>{`complete`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="pre" components={components}><MDXTag name="code" components={components} parentName="pre" props={{"className":"language-yaml"}}>{`type: Thing
id: 'https://example.com/thing/one'
name: Thing One
description: I am groot
additionalType:
- rdfs:Class
image:
- https://example.com/image/thingone.jpg
url: 'https://thingone.example.com'
identifier:
  '@context': 'https://context.yodata.io/hsf/reflex'
  UserID: '1'
    
  
`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>
           </MDXTag>
  }
}
